metadata.name: Storm Chamber | Collab with Somfay #45
metadata.description:
Generative art piece created with code in Hydra and in collaboration with artist @s0mfay

This piece arises from the absolute need to combine our styles. On the one hand, the evocative intensity of Somfay's color and that storm of shapes and movement that characterizes my work. The result is this explosive and dramatic piece that feels like a storm in a room full of liquid and high energy.

Hydra is a toolkit for live coding of network visuals created by Olivia Jack (ojack.xyz)

Collab by Somfay & Daniel Oropeza
Panama City, Panama
18/05/2022

metadata.name: Haemo Globs #302
metadata.description:
The shape and function of haematids (red blood cells) has always fascinated me. Perhaps their mathematical smoothness and candy-like aspect resonated with me as a child. Their simple appearance distinguished them from the other cell types I had learned about. I imagined them engorged with sweet-flavoured oxygen and juicily popping under my bite.

I hope for this generative artwork to communicate my appreciation for these never-ending body travellers.

metadata.name: Enlightened Journey #142
metadata.description:
A digital journey through nature.

Made in p5js

Special thanks to @Zancan and @TenebrisVia for inspiring me to code with nature, along with the work of Linda Rous for inspiring the use of perspective and stairs in the scene. Also, thanks to the FX Hash and Twitter communities for the wonderful feedback and suggestions which helped throughout the design process.
